    "ideation": "The Ear is the organ of extreme attention and selective filtering. The face acts as a sensory satellite dish. The performance starts in a state of 'background noise,' where the eyes and mouth are soft and unfocused. When a sound is detected, the animation treats the eyes as directional microphones—one eye (the 'listening' side) widens and tilts to catch the signal, while the other side narrows to cut out distractions. The mouth represents the sound wave itself: transforming from a quiet hum into a sharp, focused resonance as the signal is parsed, then finally relaxing once the message is understood. The colors move from a dormant fleshy tan to a focused, high-alert gold.",
